Associate Pricing Analyst job
in Singapore
Job Ref:
16680BR
COUNTRY:
Singapore
CITY:
Singapore
EMPLOYER:
INDUSTRY:
Sales
A Pricing Analytics role that encompasses a strong learning curve and impressive development potential for the right individual has developed. Sitting strategically within the pricing team, you will have excellent insight into the business and will partner closely with senior stakeholders within the organization on analyzing market dynamics, trends and opportunities within the industry. So Why Thermo Fisher Scientific? For starters, we are a $17 billion company with over 50,000 employees worldwide and this is an opportunity to join a truly global organization where your efforts enable us to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer. If you are looking to be part of an organization that champions progress, growth and challenges you to optimize your potential, look no further.General Summary of IPAC P&CA; Team
Analyze market dynamics, pricing trends, market opportunities, operating and sales margins in order to develop reports, procedures and tools for pricing and quoting. Works as a business partner to business leaders, drive sales, maximize profits, meet productivity standards and remain competitive with competitors. Work with global product managers and regional marketing to develop and implement product price strategies including segment strategies for the various markets and channels. Address pricing-related inquiries from sales, ensure great customers purchase experience. Provide regular and ad hoc pricing analysis and reporting for management.Minimum Qualifications (must have) Self-motivated, good at change management and comfortable with dealing with ambiguity Detail and process oriented fast learner, able to handle pressure in a fast pace complex environment Degree in Business/Finance/Marketing/Commerce/Accounting 3-7 years' experience in finance pricing role, or in a segment finance, marketing or business analysis position Strong analytical capability including strong expertise in spreadsheet (Excel) and database (Access) program Experience at manipulating and modeling data, simulation and forecasting competence is preferred Business and marketing orientation*LI-SN1 Preferred Qualifications (nice to have)Working experience in MNC company.EOE
Post Date:
05/01/2014
